text: i am no longer happy in my life
i have suffered lot because of lots of work

Lately I’ve been feeling like I’m constantly running out of energy, no matter how much I rest. Work keeps piling up, and I feel like I’m barely keeping my head above the water. Even simple tasks feel overwhelming and I don’t know how to slow down.

This week has actually been pretty refreshing. I took some time to catch up on my hobbies, spent a few hours painting, and had a peaceful evening walk. It felt really nice to just breathe and enjoy the moment without rushing anywhere.
“Yeah, everything is totally fine. I only cried three times today, but who’s counting? Honestly, I’m just tired of pretending like I’m okay.”
“I’ve been thinking deeply about life lately, not because I’m worried, but because I actually have some free time to reflect. It feels surprisingly peaceful.”
